W. Bradford (Brad) Hu 

		
		Chief Risk Officer, 

	
		 Citigroup Inc. 	

 
Last Updated: 06/19/2016 



Executive Summary
Hu is Chief Risk Officer for Citigroup Inc., one of the country’s top financial services organizations. He assumed the position in January 2013, after four years as Chief Risk Officer for Asia, where he was responsible for managing and tracking the firm’s risks across the Consumer and Institutional Clients businesses i 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Hu married Yuko Kuriyama on April 16, 1994. Their wedding was featured in the New York Times Vows column.
Hu’s father worked in the Foreign Service. 
Current Focus

Company Snapshot: Citigroup Inc. or Citi is a multinational investment banking and financial services corporation headquartered in Manhattan, New York City. Citigroup was formed from one of the world's largest merge 
Key Challenges

Compliance Settlement: A unit of Citigroup will pay $15 million to settle civil charges alleging it failed to enforce policies designed to prevent and detect insider trading, U.S. regulators said, according to an  
Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1964 in Taiwan.
Hu earned Bachelor of Science and Master of Science degrees in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science, with a concentration in Economics, from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. 
 





